<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - LUBRICATION AND SEALERS - ENGINE OIL SPECIFICATIONS -
        T444E/7.3 DIT DIESEL ENGINES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>T444E/7.3 DIT DIESEL ENGINES</title>
        <para>Use
            <emph type="bold">only</emph>those oils meeting API category CG-4/SH or CF-4/SH and CF-4/SG when CG-4/SH is
            not available. Do
            <emph type="bold">not</emph>
            use oils labeled as
            <emph type="bold">only</emph>
            SH, SG, CE or
            <emph type="bold">only</emph>
            CG-4 and CF-4 as they could cause piston ring sticking or excessive valve train wear.
        </para>
        <para>Where the minimum operating temperature is above 20&#176;F (-7&#176;C), SAE 15W-40 is the preferred
            viscosity.
        </para>
        <para>Where the temperature is consistently below 20&#176;F (-7&#176;C), the preferred oil is 10W-30.</para>
    </svcproc>
